This paper is about medical image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed Phase Collaborative Network (PCN) is an end-to-end framework that contains both generative and discriminative modules, which suggests that it may involve machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also mentions that the experiments are performed on a two-phase CT dataset, which implies that it may involve multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to address the challenge of fusing prediction from two phases, which may involve neural networks (cs.NE) or other related techniques.
